Preheat oven to 450 degrees F. Heat olive oil in 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium-high heat and cook shrimp with red pepper flakes, turning once, 2 minutes or until shrimp turn pink. Arrange pizza crust on ungreased baking sheet. Evenly top with 1/2 cup sauce, then artichokes, tomatoes and cooked shrimp. Top with remaining sauce, then sprinkle with cheese. Bake 12 minutes or until cheese is melted.